cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.SD, cs.NA, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with image processing and blind deconvolution techniques for astronomical images. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the problem of estimating the PSF and a denoised image, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions noise canceling and promoting the whiteness of the residual, which are techniques used in audio signal processing. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also possible as the paper proposes a blind deconvolution scheme that relies on image regularization and wavelet analysis, which are numerical techniques. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a method that does not assume a parametric model of the PSF and can be applied to any telescope, which involves machine learning and AI concepts.
